<l>ēṉai yekiṉē yakaram varumē</l>
<l>valleḻut tiyaṟkai mikutal vēṇṭum</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When <foreign xml:lang="ta">ekiṉ</foreign> denotes a tree, it is of the same nature of <foreign xml:lang="ta">āṇ</foreign> a tree.<note
              place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">Ekiṉ</foreign> means either ' the tamarind tree ',
          or ' swan ' ; when glossed ' swan ', it gets <foreign xml:lang="ta">a</foreign> and the
          doubling of the following plosive, cf. 338.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
